                    line2_4: "Dermatology: diseases of skins such as eczema, nettle rash, burn, frostbite etc.",
                    line2_5: "Pediatrics: deals with children (from babies and infants to teenager) and their illness",
                    line2_6: "Obstetrics and Gynecology: illness peculiar to women, pregnancy and birth",
                    line2_7: "Otolaryngologist (ENT): diseases and illness of the ears, nose and throat",
                    line2_8: "Ophthalmology: diseases of the eyes",
                    line2_9: "Psychiatry: mental illness such as depression, anorexia, panic disorder etc.",
                    line2_10: "Plastic surgery: burn, frostbite, spot, mark, cosmetic surgery etc.",
                    text2_1: "Please make sure that you know the types of medical institutions in your neighborhood and what kind of treatment they offer. In case you don't know which institution to visit, please check your symptom referring the list above and consult the medical institution nearby, equipped with the department you think you need to visit, first by phone.",
                    link2_1: 'Tokyo Metropolitan Medical Institution Information "Himawari"."',
                    text2_2: "Although large general hospitals and hospitals in affiliation with universities have every kind of departments, the problem is that it's highly possible that you have to wait for quite a long time there. Moreover, without an introduction card written by a doctor of your neighborhood, the doctor's fee will be higher. Therefore, to see a doctor in your neighborhood will be best for the first step. If that hospital or clinic wasn't enough, the next step will be asking the doctor to write an introduction card and then go to a large general hospital.",
                    text2_3: '* Medical Institutions equipped with more than 20 beds are called "hospitals (byouin)", those with less than 19 beds are called "clinic (sinnryoujo, clinic, or iin in Japanese)".',
                    title3: "What to do if hospitalization is needed?",
                    text3_1: "If you are told that you need to be hospitalized, please follow the instruction of the hospital. In general, they'll ask you things listed below:",
                    line3_1:"application form, agreement",
                    line3_2:"hospital identification card",
                    line3_3:"health insurance card",
                    line3_4:"seal",
                    text3_2:"Moreover, when going into the hospital, guarantee and a deposit are required. Generally you'll ask your relatives, your school teacher or your boss to be your guarantee. If you cannot find anyone to ask, please consult the hospital. In some cases, paying additional deposit will make you entering the hospital without a guarantee. A deposit is usually between 50,000 yen to 100,000 yen. When getting out of the hospital, it'll be calculated as hospital charges and be adjusted, which means you need to keep all kind of deposit receipt till you get out.",
                    text3_3:"In addition, you need to prepare things listed below when going into the hospital:",
